## About IMiN
IMiN is a national hub for Mining 4.0 excellence, established at TEXMiN, IIT (ISM) Dhanbad, in collaboration with Coal India Limited (CIL). The centre integrates digital innovation, advanced automation, and sustainable practices across the mining and energy sectors. IMiN accelerates technology development, rapid field deployment, and interdisciplinary research, while nurturing entrepreneurial talent and supporting start-up incubation.
Activities at IMiN span cutting-edge R&D, pilot-scale implementation, skills development, and capacity building. The centre empowers the next generation of mining professionals through substantial fellowship programs, hands-on workshops, and industry-driven training. IMiN’s ecosystem brings together leading researchers, industry partners, and start-ups to advance India’s self-reliance in sustainable mining and energy.

### About IIT (ISM)
The Indian Institute of Technology (Indian School of Mines), Dhanbad — established in 1926 — is one of India’s premier institutions of national importance. Originally founded to address the need for skilled manpower in mining and earth sciences, IIT (ISM) has since evolved into a multidisciplinary institute offering cutting-edge education and research across engineering, applied sciences, management, and humanities.

### Vision
To transform India’s mining ecosystem into a digitally empowered, safe, and sustainable industry. IMiN envisions a future where data-driven decision making, automation, and digital collaboration redefine efficiency and environmental responsibility across mining operations.

